travene Sections 287 and 411 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. The Chief Magistrate, Mrs S.K. Matepo, admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N250,000 with two sureties in like sum. Matepo adjourned the case until Jan. 20 for mention. [NAN] Vanguard News Nigeria. Lagos—The police, yesterday, charged a 32-year-old female banker, Adejumoke Anthony, who allegedly aided some fraudsters to steal N90 million from a customer of the bank before an Igbosere Magistrates’ Court, in Lagos. December 3, 2015 In "News" A 20-year-old househelp , Faith Edeh, who was alleged to have stolen her employer’s jewellery and other items worth N20 million, was yesterday arraigned before an Igbosere Magistrates’ Court in Lagos. Edeh was arraigned alongside one Peter Obah, 37, the agent that brought her to her employer. January 23, 2016 In "News" Lagos—A 48-year-old estate agent, Olalekan Biodun, who allegedly stole N2.7 million from EcoBank Plc, was yesterday charged before a Lagos Magistrate’s Court sitting at Igbosere. August 16, 2016 In "News"